legacy.name: The Chinese Way

result.text:
Delicate and enchanting, China's traditional handmade artistry - the Ronghua (Chinese: 绒花), or velvet flower, crafted meticulously from natural silk, portrays auspicious blooms in both ceremonial rituals and everyday adornments. 
The art tracing back to the Tang Dynasty (618-907) used to be a prestigious tribute to the imperial court. Its name derived from the harmonious sound of Chinese characters “荣华”, which symbolizes prosperity and good fortune. It stands as a testament to unrivaled craftsmanship, requiring dozens of intricate steps that defy mechanization. 
Across various regions of China, schools of Ronghua have emerged, such as the celebrated styles of Nanjing and Beijing, each embodying distinct cultural nuances.
#Chineseway #culturalheritage #velvetflower #Chineseart @DiscoverNanjing @SpotlightBJ @Chinacultureorg @ChinaCulture8
